/**
 * This ruleset defines the security model for a public wedding guest book.
 *
 * Core Philosophy:
 * The security model is designed to be open for reading and new contributions
 * but strict about modifications. It follows a "write-once, read-many" pattern.
 * Anyone, including unauthenticated visitors, can view all guest book entries.
 * Any authenticated user, including those signed in anonymously, can create a new
 * entry. Once an entry is created, it is immutable and cannot be updated or
 * deleted by anyone, which prevents vandalism and preserves the integrity of the guest book.
 *
 * Data Structure:
 * The data is organized in a single top-level collection:
 * - /guest_book_entries/{guestBookEntryId}: Stores all guest book messages.
 *
 * Key Security Decisions:
 * - Public Read Access: All entries in `guest_book_entries` are publicly readable
 *   to allow any visitor to see the guest book.
 * - Authenticated Creation: To prevent abuse and spam, only authenticated users
 *   (including anonymous users) can create new entries. This provides a minimal
 *   layer of protection while still allowing broad participation.
 * - Immutability: Update and delete operations are explicitly disallowed for all
 *   users. This ensures that once a message is posted, it cannot be altered or
 *   removed, securing the guest book's content.
 *
 * Denormalization for Authorization:
 * This data model is very simple and does not require denormalization for
 * authorization, as all security decisions are based on the user's
 * authentication state rather than on relationships between documents.
 *
 * Structural Segregation:
 * Not applicable, as all guest book entries share the same public visibility.
 * There is no distinction between private and public data.
 */
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    // Helper Functions
    /**
     * Checks if the user is authenticated, including anonymous sign-ins.
     */
    function isSignedIn() {
      return request.auth != null;
    }

    /**
     * @description
     * Manages access to guest book entries. Allows anyone to read all entries and
     * any authenticated user (including anonymous) to create a new entry.
     * Entries are immutable and cannot be changed or deleted once created.
     * @path /guest_book_entries/{guestBookEntryId}
     * @allow (get) Any user, signed-in or not, can read a specific guest book entry.
     * @allow (create) A user who is signed in anonymously can create a new entry.
     * @deny (update) Any user attempts to update an existing entry. This is denied.
     * @deny (delete) Any user attempts to delete an existing entry. This is denied.
     * @principle Implements a 'write-once, read-many' public data model, preventing vandalism by making documents immutable after creation.
     */
    match /guest_book_entries/{guestBookEntryId} {
      // READ: Anyone can read guest book entries.
      allow get: if true;
      allow list: if true;

      // WRITE: Only authenticated users can create. No one can update or delete.
      allow create: if isSignedIn();
      allow update: if false;
      allow delete: if false;
    }
  }
}